instruction.text:
For securing your company, it is important to start with proper asset management.

You can, after all, only secure what you know that you have.

In general, in information security it is vital to know what you have and where you have it. You'll want to focus your efforts on those areas of your company that are vital to your business and where an attack would hurt you most. Knowing your systems also enables you to effectively manage threat intelligence - does the latest big news affect you or are you not using anything vulnerable? Having this information is also the first step towards automating your defenses. If you can list all the servers you have here, you can use that list in automated scans that will tell you the most glaring vulnerabilities you could be affected by, offering more low-hanging fruit to improve the cyber-security of your company.
